      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (NIH, RH index) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint of hemolysis risk.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the FDA-recommended QoI for pump hemolysis assessment and is directly correlated with plasma-free hemoglobin elevation, the clinical marker for hemolytic injury. The relative hemolysis index (RH < 1) criterion is consistent with FDA guidance for comparative hemolysis assessment."
    },
