      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; selection of turbulence and hemolysis sub-models must be justified.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model and Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model were selected based on published literature for centrifugal blood pump CFD. Model form uncertainty assessment beyond this literature justification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, boundary conditions) must be documented with sources and nominal values; variability ranges must be reported.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs were documented in the simulation report: pump geometry from CAD files (traceable to manufacturing drawings), blood analog viscosity from rheometer measurements (3.5 ± 0.2 cP), inlet flow rates from calibrated flow meters (±2%), rotational speed from encoder feedback (±10 RPM). Variability ranges are reported; propagation of these uncertainties through Monte Carlo sampling confirmed that output NIH uncertainty is ±11% at 95% confidence. Note: identification of which input parameters are the dominant drivers of NIH variability is planned for a subsequent sensitivity analysis phase but has not yet been completed."
    },
