    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors met or exceeded the required level for MRL 2. Six factors were appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. Uncertainty quantification was performed, yielding ±11% NIH uncertainty at 95% confidence across the five operating points. The model satisfies the RH < 1 acceptance criterion for all operating conditions. The credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory decision for this Class II CPB device. A sensitivity analysis to characterize dominant input drivers is planned for a future revision.",
